[SN]TITLE[SN]
Spring 2017 'warmest on record for Northern Ireland'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Spring 2017 has been the warmest on record for Northern Ireland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The mean temperature from 1 March - 31 May was 9.2C - that is 1.3C above the seasonal average.
The season also recorded 112% of normal sunshine hours at 478.4 hours.
Just 82% average rainfall fell during the three-month period with 198.1mm recorded.
The records date back to 1910. Overall, spring 2017 for the UK as a whole has ranked second warmest on record.
